  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development to examine the influence of blood viscosity and power-law index on the relative hemolysis index; results confirmed that the baseline parametric choices were conservative. No formal uncertainty quantification campaign was deemed necessary given the MRL 2 classification and the corroborating bench-test data.",
